problem.markdown:
>>What is the main problem with fairness through unawareness? <<
( ) Unfairness is due to the model. {{Unfairness arises from unfair data, and not from the model itself. }}
( ) It is a form of direct discrimination. {{It is a form of indirect discrimination. }}
(x) The protected attributes could be encoded in non-sensitive features. {{In fairness through unawareness, one ignores the protected attributes (for example, race), and makes a prediction based on non-sensitive features (for example, area code).  The main problem is that the protected attributes could be encoded in the non-sensitive features, which could then not guarantee a fair classification.}}
( ) We have to define two similarity metrics: one for the individuals, and one for the outcomes. {{This is a problem with fairness through awareness, not unawareness. }}

